---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import FAQSchema from "../../../components/FAQSchema.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Tile & Grout Cleaning | Montreal, Laval, South Shore"
  description="Professional high-pressure tile and grout cleaning. We restore your joints' original color and apply a protective sealant. Montreal, Laval & South Shore. Free quote."
>
  <!-- SPLIT SCREEN HERO (Standardized) -->
  <div class="split-hero-container">
    <div class="container full-width-split">
      <div class="split-layout">
        <!-- LEFT COLUMN: CONTENT -->
        <div class="split-content fade-in-section">
          <span class="service-cat-badge">HARD SURFACES</span>
          <h1 class="split-title fade-in-up text-gradient-empire">
            Tile & Grout Cleaning
          </h1>

          <div class="problem-statement fade-in-up delay-100">
            <h3 class="problem-title">The Problem:</h3>
            <p class="problem-text">
              Grout lines are porous. Over the years, they absorb dirty mop water, grease in the kitchen, and soap scum in the bathroom. Your light grout turns black, and no amount of scrubbing seems to work anymore.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="lead-text fade-in-up delay-200">
            Stop exhausting yourself scrubbing on your knees! Our mobile <strong>high-pressure truck-mount unit</strong> (up to 1200 PSI) combined with specialized alkaline solutions literally extracts embedded dirt, bringing your joints back to their original color.
          </p>

          <div class="cta-group fade-in-up delay-300">
            <a href="tel:5148939939" class="btn btn-primary pulse-btn">
              <span class="icon">📞</span> (514) 893-9939
            </a>
            <button onclick="window.openEstimationWidget()" class="btn btn-outline-reveal">
              <span class="icon">⚡</span> Instant Free Quote
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT COLUMN: IMAGE (Carousel) -->
        <div class="split-image-wrapper fade-in-section delay-200">
          <div class="slideshow-container">
            <img
              src="/images/catalog/tuiles.webp"
              alt="High pressure ceramic tile cleaning Montreal - Empire Group"
              class="slide active"
              width="1200"
              height="800"
              fetchpriority="high"
              loading="eager"
            />
            <img
              src="/images/catalog/photo-41.webp"
              alt="Grout restoration before after - Laval"
              class="slide"
              width="1200"
              height="800"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <img
              src="/images/catalog/tuile-cleaner-optimized.webp"
              alt="Professional tile cleaning equipment"
              class="slide"
              width="1200"
              height="800"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <img
              src="/images/catalog/tuile-card-optimized.webp"
              alt="Grout deep cleaning South Shore"
              class="slide"
              width="1200"
              height="800"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <img
              src="/images/catalog/tuile-main.webp"
              alt="Ceramic floor cleaning expert Montreal"
              class="slide"
              width="1200"
              height="800"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="image-overlay-gradient"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container alternate-layout">
      <div class="service-main-content">
        
        <div class="info-block">
          <h2 class="text-gradient-empire">Why traditional mopping doesn't work</h2>
          <p>When you wash your floor with a standard mop, the water quickly becomes dirty. Because the grout lines are slightly lower than the tile surface, the dirty water pools in these crevices. As the water evaporates, the dirt and soap residue remain trapped in the porous grout.</p>
          <p>This is exactly why your grout lines darken over time, especially in high-traffic areas like the kitchen and main hallway. Only <strong>industrial pressurized extraction</strong> can flush out this accumulated dirt.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- PROCESSUS -->
        <div class="process-section" style="margin-top: 4rem;">
          <h2 class="text-gradient-empire">Our 5-Step Deep Cleaning Process</h2>
          <div class="process-steps">
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <div class="step-text">
                <h3>Thorough Inspection</h3>
                <p>We analyze the type of tile (ceramic, porcelain, natural stone) and the condition of the grout to determine the appropriate chemical solution and pressure level.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <div class="step-text">
                <h3>Alkaline Solution Application</h3>
                <p>We spray a professional-grade, eco-friendly alkaline cleaner that breaks down grease, oil, and deeply embedded dirt (Dwell time: 10 to 15 minutes).</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <div class="step-text">
                <h3>High-Pressure Wash & Extraction</h3>
                <p>Using our truck-mounted system and a specialized floor tool, we blast hot water (up to 1200 PSI) while simultaneously extracting the water and dirt. The enclosed tool prevents splattering on your walls and cabinets.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <div class="step-text">
                <h3>Detail Scrubbing (If Necessary)</h3>
                <p>For particularly stubborn areas, corners, and baseboards, we perform targeted manual scrubbing with specialized grout brushes.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-num">5</div>
              <div class="step-text">
                <h3>Protective Sealant (Optional)</h3>
                <p>Once the grout is perfectly clean and dry, we highly recommend applying a transparent sealant. This creates a waterproof barrier, preventing future spills from penetrating the porous grout lines.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- VISIBLE EDUCATIONAL CONTENT -->
        <div style="margin-top: 3rem;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.4rem;">The Importance of Grout Sealer</h3>
          <p style="line-height: 1.7; color: #444; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Unsealed grout is like a sponge. If you spill coffee, red wine, or cooking oil, it will immediately soak in and cause a permanent stain. After our deep cleaning, your grout is clean but vulnerable.</p>
          <p style="line-height: 1.7; color: #444;">We offer a <strong>professional clear sealer application</strong>. This invisible barrier fills the microscopic pores of the grout. The next time you drop liquid, it will bead on the surface instead of penetrating, giving you ample time to wipe it up without leaving a trace.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- PLACES WE CLEAN -->
        <div style="margin-top: 3rem; background: #f8fbff; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid #dce8f5;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; font-size: 1.4rem;">✨ Common areas we restore</h3>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li><strong>Kitchens:</strong> Eliminates cooking grease buildup and embedded food spills.</li>
            <li><strong>Bathrooms:</strong> Removes soap scum, hard water deposits, and mildew from shower walls and floors.</li>
            <li><strong>Entryways & Hallways:</strong> Extracts winter salt, mud, and heavy foot-traffic dirt.</li>
            <li><strong>Commercial Spaces:</strong> Restaurants, offices, and retail stores requiring high hygiene standards.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <!-- SERVICED ZONES -->
        <div class="zones-section" style="margin-top: 4rem;">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.4rem;">Service Areas — Tile Cleaning</h3>
          <p>We travel anywhere in the Greater Montreal Area with our high-pressure mobile units.</p>

          <div class="city-group">
            <p class="city-lead">🏙️ Montreal (East & West)</p>
            <div class="badges-container">
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Montreal (all boroughs)</span>
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Westmount</span>
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Mount Royal</span>
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Outremont</span>
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 LaSalle</span>
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 And much more...</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="city-group">
            <p class="city-lead">🏘️ Laval</p>
            <div class="badges-container">
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Laval (entire city)</span>
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Chomedey</span>
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Sainte-Rose</span>
              <span class="badge badge-blue">📍 Vimont</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="city-group">
            <p class="city-lead">🌿 Montreal South Shore</p>
            <div class="badges-container">
              <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Longueuil</span>
              <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Brossard</span>
              <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Saint-Lambert</span>
              <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Saint-Hubert</span>
              <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Greenfield Park</span>
              <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Saint-Bruno</span>
              <span class="badge badge-green">📍 Boucherville</span>
              <span class="badge badge-green">📍 And much more...</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <p class="contact-footer">Need a quick appointment? Call us at <strong>(514) 893-9939</strong>.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ with Schema Component -->
          <FAQSchema
            title="Frequently Asked Questions — Tile & Grout Cleaning"
            faqs={[
              {
                question: "Do you use harsh chemicals (like bleach or acid) to clean grout?",
                answer: "No. We primarily use professional alkaline-based eco-friendly solutions to break down grease and dirt. We avoid harsh acids that can degrade the structural integrity of your grout over time, and we never use bleach, which only hides dirt by bleaching it rather than removing it.",
              },
              {
                question: "Will the high pressure damage my tiles or blow out the grout lines?",
                answer: "No, our technicians are highly trained to adjust the water pressure (PSI) according to the condition of your floor. While our truck-mount can reach very high pressures, we often clean at lower, safe pressures (around 800 - 1000 PSI) which is more than enough to blast dirt out of pores without causing any damage to sound grout.",
              },
              {
                question: "Can you change the color of my grout?",
                answer: "Our standard cleaning restores the grout to its original color by removing the dirt on top. If your grout was originally dark grey, it will remain dark grey. We do not currently offer 'color sealing' (painting the grout lines a new color).",
              },
              {
                question: "How often should I have my ceramic floors professionally cleaned?",
                answer: "For a typical household, every 12 to 18 months is recommended to maintain the brightness of the grout and extend its lifespan. For commercial spaces or homes with many pets, every 6 months might be necessary.",
              },
              {
                question: "Do I need to stay off the floor after you apply the sealer?",
                answer: "We recommend staying off the sealed floor for at least 2 to 4 hours to allow the sealer to dry properly. It fully cures in about 24 hours, during which time you should avoid spilling any liquids on the floor.",
              },
              {
                question: "Is there a lot of water splashing during the process?",
                answer: "None at all. We use a specialized enclosed rotary tool (often called a 'spinner' or 'sx-15'). The high-pressure jets are completely encased under a dome, and the water is extracted immediately in the same motion. Your baseboards and cabinets are completely safe from splashing.",
              },
            ]}
          />
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- SIDEBAR -->
      <aside class="service-sidebar">
        <div class="sticky-cta">
          <h3>Free Estimate</h3>
          <a href="tel:5148939939" class="btn btn-primary full-width">(514) 893-9939</a>
          <button onclick="window.openEstimationWidget()" class="btn btn-outline full-width">Online Estimate</button>
          <div class="guarantee">⭐ High-Pressure Technology</div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* HERO SPLIT LAYOUT (Standardized) */
  .split-hero-container {
    background-color: #fff;
    padding-top: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    width: 100vw;
  }
  .full-width-split { width: 100%; max-width: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .split-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    align-items: stretch;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }
  .split-content {
    background-color: #ffffff;
    padding: 100px 4rem 4rem 10%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .service-cat-badge {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .split-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 3.5vw, 3.8rem);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .problem-statement {
    background: #ffffff;
    border-left: 4px solid #ff4444;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(174, 206, 235, 0.3);
  }
  .problem-title { font-size: 1rem; color: #cc0000; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 700; }
  .problem-text { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--color-text-main); font-style: italic; }
  .lead-text { font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-main); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; max-width: 650px; }
  .cta-group { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .split-image-wrapper { position: relative; height: 100%; min-height: 500px; width: 100%; overflow: hidden; }
  .slideshow-container { position: relative; width: 100%; height: 100%; overflow: hidden; }
  .slide { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 1.5s ease-in-out; }
  .slide.active { opacity: 1; }
  .image-overlay-gradient { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.2), transparent); pointer-events: none; z-index: 2; }

  /* BUTTON STYLES (Standardized) */
  .btn-outline-reveal {
    background: transparent; border: 2px solid var(--color-primary); color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 4px; transition: all 0.3s ease; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .btn-outline-reveal:hover { background: var(--color-primary); color: white; transform: translateY(-2px); }

  .content-section { padding: 5rem 0; }
  .alternate-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 350px; gap: 4rem; }
  .info-block h2 { font-size: 2.2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .info-block p { line-height: 1.7; color: #444; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .check-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .check-list li { padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.75rem; position: relative; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0; }
  .check-list li::before { content: "✓"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: #2e7d32; font-weight: bold; }

  /* ZONES */
  .city-group { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .city-lead { font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-primary); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .badges-container { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .badge { padding: 0.4rem 0.9rem; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 0.9rem; border: 1px solid transparent; }
  .badge-blue { background: #e8f4fd; border-color: #c5dff0; }
  .badge-green { background: #f0faf0; border-color: #b8ddb8; }
  .contact-footer { margin-top: 1.5rem; font-style: italic; color: #666; }

  /* PROCESS */
  .process-steps { margin-top: 2rem; }
  .step { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .step-num { min-width: 32px; height: 32px; background: var(--color-primary); color: white; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: bold; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 5px; }
  .step-text h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .step-text p { color: #555; line-height: 1.5; }

  /* SIDEBAR */
  .sticky-cta { position: sticky; top: 100px; background: white; border: 1px solid #eee; padding: 2rem; border-radius: 15px; box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); text-align: center; }
  .sticky-cta h3 { margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-primary); }
  .sticky-cta p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: #666; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .guarantee { margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: bold; color: #2e7d32; }

  @media (max-width: 992px) {
    .split-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .alternate-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .split-title { font-size: 2.2rem; }
    .split-image-wrapper { height: 400px; min-height: 0; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Slideshow Logic
  const slides = document.querySelectorAll(".slide");
  let currentSlide = 0;

  function nextSlide() {
    slides[currentSlide].classList.remove("active");
    currentSlide = (currentSlide + 1) % slides.length;
    slides[currentSlide].classList.add("active");
  }

  if (slides.length > 1) {
    setInterval(nextSlide, 4000); // 4 seconds
  }
</script>
